The paper discusses techniques for inducing discriminative features for multiclass classification, which is a common problem in machine learning. The use of second order structure in the data suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), or cs.ST (Statistics). The focus on theoretical properties and empirical performance suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
